{
  "texts": [
    "Yet almost all of them target comprehensive video understanding, with little regard for interpretability.",
    "Related benchmarks such as VIP (Himakunthala et al., 2023) and NExT-GQA (Xiao et al., 2024) are thus valuable efforts in developing trustworthy Video-LLM techniques and deserve more research attention.",
    "From a modeling perspective, VideoQA models are imbalanced in terms of their language and visual representations.",
    "The language encoders are drawn from ever-larger and more powerful language models which dominate over comparatively weaker visual representations, where CLIP Radford et al. (2021) and its variants Ilharco et al. (2021); Sun et al. (2023) remain defacto standards even though they struggle to represent fine-grained details.",
    "More importantly, from an image to a video level, the temporal and dynamic modeling tends to be primitive."
  ]
}